e rules of the physical world…\n\n- Belsebuub, The Astral Codex: Out-of-Body Experiences and Lucid Dreaming for Spiritual Knowledge\n|\nAs long as we’re breathing, we have a chance to start over and build a stable future.\n\n- Kim Ha Campbell, Inner Peace Outer Abundance\n|\nTo be productive, you have to stop being absent-minded\n\n- Sunday\n|\nIf you start by promising what you don't even have yet, you'll lose your desire to work towards getting it.\n\n- Paulo Coelho, The Alchemist\n|\nWe do not escape our boundaries or our innermost being. We do not change. It is true we may be transformed, but we always walk within our boundaries, within the marked-off circle.\n\n- Ernst Jünger, The Glass Bees\n|\nWe often seek beauty in the outside, in the unknown, and often lack to realize the sheer beauty right in front of our very eyes, back home.\n\n- Akilnathan\n|\nDespite all of the violence, suffering and wars, don’t forget to sing the song of love, harmony, and peace.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nTough times don't define you, they refine you. ‪\n\n- Carlos A.  Rodriguez, Designed For Inheritance: A Discovery of Sonship\n|\nWith persistent perseverance, you can break through any barrier.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nThe oceans and seas are forces which, if you forget, they will gladly remind you.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nOn a mental level, kindness and compassion give rise to lasting joy.\n\n- Auliq-Ice\n|\nSoul-to-soul contact sweeps through, like a tsunami, leaving in its wake just this: unconditional surrender and overwhelming gentleness.\n\n- Laurie Nadel, Dancing with the Wind: A True Story of Zen in the Art of Windsurfing\n|\nO I never thought that joys would run away from boys,Or that boys would change their minds and forsake such summer joys;But alack I never dreamed that the world had other toys\n\n- John Clare, Poems Chiefly from Manuscript"